疫情下的武汉“守夜人”。
Wuhan "night watchman" under the epidemic situation.
陈亮。
Chen Liang.
南方人物周刊                      。
Southern Character Week.
南方人物周刊。
Southern Character Week.
2月的春光已经露出些明媚，但每当入夜，疫情下的武汉依然春寒料峭，霜寒刺骨。
February's spring has been a little bright, but every night, the epidemic situation in Wuhan is still chilly cold, frost piercing.
医护人员夜以继日地奋战在战“疫”一线，“宅家”的市民们或已进入梦乡，在城市的街头巷尾，还有一群“守夜人”出入于寒风中。
Day and night medical personnel are fighting the "epidemic" line, "homestead citizens have either fallen asleep, in the city's streets and alleys, and a group of" night watchmen "in and out of the cold.
黎明不远，终将来临。
The dawn is near and it will come.
黎明前的至暗时刻，这宁静的夜晚，正是他们在守护本文首发于南方人物周刊2020年第4期图、文 | 陈亮  编辑 | 方迎忠 郑洁全文约2172，细读大约需要5分钟消杀毒工人聂和平48岁聂和平负责洪山体育馆方舱医院北门（体育馆路）的清扫保洁和消毒工作。
In the darkest hour before dawn, this peaceful night, it is they who are guarding the cleanup and disinfection of the North Gate (Stadium Road) of Hung Shan Sports Centre, Fang Ming Hospital (Stadium Road), a 48-year-old antivirus worker.
“感觉武汉疫情严重，整个城市太安静了。
"Wuhan is so bad, the whole city is too quiet.
武汉限制出行后，每天上上班，是最开心了，能出去走走。
Wuhan restricted travel, every day to work, is the happiest, can go out for a walk.
面对疫情最重要的是保持乐观心态，我还年轻，抵抗力强，我不怕！”聂和平说，“等疫情结束后，我要好好休息两天，带上家人把武汉好好转转，平时太忙了。
The most important thing is to maintain an optimistic attitude, I am still young, strong resistance, I am not afraid! "Nie said," after the epidemic, I will have a good rest for two days, take my family to Wuhan, usually too busy.
”急救医生王科王科是武汉市急救中心“肺炎急救”专班成员，每天下午4：30至第二天早上8：30负责120急救工作。
First-aid doctor Wang Kaoke, a member of Wuhan First Aid Center's "First Aid Pneumonia" class, was in charge of 120 first-aid cases from 4.30 p.m. to 8.30 a.m. the next day.
“疫情发生以来，整个城市街道寥寥数人，每天武汉三镇忙于接送急救病人，心里倍感失落。
"Since the outbreak of the epidemic, the whole city streets few people, every day Wuhan three towns busy to transport the emergency patients, feel frustrated.
”王科感叹道。
"sighed Wang.
“平日工作里，遇到低血糖病人，通过急救让病人苏醒，我就特有成就感。
"On weekdays, I feel a sense of accomplishment when I encounter patients with hypoglycemia who are awakened by first aid.
现在跟新冠肺炎患者一起，除了帮助病人保持呼吸畅通，还要多做心理辅导，给他们加油鼓劲！”120调度员陈蕾疫情发生后，武汉市急救中心工作量剧增。
Now, along with patients with pneumonia, in addition to helping patients keep breathing smooth, but also to do more psychological counseling, to cheer them up! 120 dispatcher Chen Lei outbreak, Wuhan City, the workload of the emergency center increased dramatically.
120调度员陈蕾每天晚上8点至早上8点工作不停歇。
120 dispatcher Chen Lei works from 8am to 8am every night.
“每天，呼吸道疾病的呼叫量比例大，各类急诊重症病例上升。
"Every day there is a high proportion of calls for respiratory illnesses and an increase in serious cases of all types of emergencies.
经常遇到接送的病人无法正常入院，特殊时期，救护车需辗转几个医院。
Frequently encountered transport patients can not be properly admitted to hospital, special periods, ambulances have to run through several hospitals.
我要快速地将接收医院找到，让病人入院。
I'm gonna get the hospital fast, get the patient into the hospital.
每当病人成功入院，我都特别欣慰。
Every time the patient was admitted to the hospital, I was particularly pleased.
”陈蕾说，“等疫情结束，我要好好睡个觉。
"When the outbreak is over, I want to get a good sleep.
”酒店店长刘蕾90后刘蕾是布丁酒店抗击疫情战队队长，酒店离医院比较近，于是成为省妇幼保健院、陆军总医院、672医院等医院前线医护人员的住宿点。
After Liu Lei 90, the head of the Pudding Hotel's anti-epidemic team, the hotel is closer to the hospital and has become a front-line hospital for hospital staff such as provincial maternal and child health care, army general hospital and 672 hospitals.
“一天晚上，我正在吃泡面，一位医生从医院里带了个馒头给我，也没有留言，感觉挺暖的。
"One night while I was eating noodles, a doctor brought me a steamed bun from the hospital.
元宵节他们从医院里带汤圆给我们吃，说我们辛苦了。
On Lantern Festival, they bring us soup Yuan from the hospital to eat, saying that we have worked hard.
”便利店员工吕梦婷便利店每天保持24小时营业，28岁的吕梦婷上夜班的次数比较多，晚上8点到第二天早上8点。
Convenience-store employee Lv Mengting stayed open 24 hours a day, with Lv Mengting, 28, working more nights from 8pm to 8am.
父母和弟弟都在孝感，她跟男朋友在武汉。
Her parents and younger brother are filial, she and her boyfriend in Wuhan.
“不管你做哪个行业，都要承担起责任，疫情前也会上夜班，其实是一样的。
"No matter what industry you do, you have to take responsibility. Before the epidemic, there was night work, but it was the same.
现在我们周围没有开店的，感觉对顾客实现了承诺，始终留着这盏灯。
Now we do not have a shop around, feel to the customer fulfilled the promise, always keep this lamp.
”蔬果加工员王花疫情期间，武汉美菜网蔬果加工员王花的工作量突然增加，基本是加了四个小时左右，最长的一次从上午11点工作到了第二天11点。
During the outbreak of Wang Flower, a vegetable and fruit processor at Wuhan Meat Net, the workload for Wang Hua, the greengrocer, increased abruptly by about four hours, with the longest one working from 11 a.m. to 11 a.m. the next day.
“原来打包分拣，我们二十多个人分拣一万多个包裹。
"Originally packed and sorted, more than twenty of us sorted out more than 10,000 parcels.
现在人少，十几个人来分，所以压力也大一些。
There are fewer people and a dozen people to divide, so the pressure is higher.
因为人员不够，还需要进行筛果的工作。
There is also a need to sift through the fruit because of insufficient personnel.
但我们在这里吃得很好，比在家里吃的还要好。
But we eat well here, better than at home.
”菜品配送司机刘浪刘浪是湖北荆门人，在武汉疫情最严重的时候，回到武汉，想要给这座城市帮帮忙。
"Liu Longgang, a food distribution driver from Hubei Province, returned to Wuhan at the height of the epidemic to help the city.
“自己在家的时候，看各种新闻报道，感人的一线医护事迹，看到一个市长在一线工作然后被感染了，当时觉得很感动。
"When I was at home, I was moved to see the news stories, the touching stories of first-line medical care, the sight of a mayor working on the front line and getting infected.
我在家有物资储备，但因为疫情武汉的饭店商户基本关门，就会担心武汉的居民都吃啥……反正自己在家也没事，就来干呗。
I have material reserves at home, but because the epidemic situation in Wuhan hotel merchants basically closed, will worry about what Wuhan residents eat... anyway no matter at home, do it.
”早餐面点厨师沈师傅疫情期间，沈师傅负责为附近方舱医院、援汉医疗团队的医务人员准备每日三餐，凌晨3点上班，一直工作到下午五六点。
Breakfast noodle chef Master Shen was in charge of preparing three meals a day for medical staff from the nearby cabin hospital and the medical aid team until 5pm.
沈师傅18岁当过兵，那年正是汶川地震，虽然没被派去支援，但是每天看到新闻和前线发来的消息就很想也出一份力。
Shen Shifu was a soldier at the age of 18. It was Wenchuan earthquake that year. Although he was not sent to support him, he wanted to contribute to the daily news and news from the front line.
“一个当过兵的人在这种时刻的感受就是，在家里待不住。
"The feeling of a soldier at a time like this is that you can't stay at home.
躺在家里看到新闻，就想马上过来看能帮什么忙。
Lying at home and reading the news, I wanted to come and see what I could do.
”外卖小哥张程张程瞒着妈妈做了骑手，疫情期间每天接单可达到80-90单，送单成绩居区域前三。
"Brother Zhang Cheng Zhang Cheng became a rider without her mother's knowledge, reaching 80 to 90 tickets a day during the epidemic, placing him in the top three spot in the region.
为了方便工作，他之前每天会煮五六个水煮蛋吃，现在已经要吃十个了。
He used to boil five or six boiled eggs a day to make it easier to work, and now he has to eat ten.
“工作上成就感最强。
You feel the strongest at work.
前些天给江苏医疗团队送物资。
A few days ago sent supplies to Jiangsu medical team.
那个单子只有我拿到了，觉得给这些逆行的白衣天使送东西，挺光荣的。
I was the only one who got that list, and I thought it was a great honor to give something to these retrograde white angels.
”长江大桥交警刘升长江大桥交警大队一中队副中队长刘升今年38岁，妻子和6岁的孩子在疫情前回海南过年了，他原计划封城当天到海南和家人团聚。
Liu Sheng, vice-captain of a squadron of traffic police at the Changjiang Bridge, was 38 years old when his wife and six-year-old children returned to Hainan for the Lunar New Year before the outbreak.
“曾经的长江大桥，车多得需要分单双号通行，每天行人游客众多，现在几乎没车没人走。
"There used to be a great number of cars on the Yangtze River Bridge. There were so many pedestrians every day that almost no cars left.
疫情期间，有个老人从汉口那边步行去武昌给女儿送物资，走到长江大桥就累得不行了。
During the outbreak, an old man walked from Hankou to Wuchang to deliver supplies to his daughter.
当时我发现了，就帮他给送过去了。
When I found out, I sent it to him.
武汉封城交通中断，的确给大家出行带来很大的困难。
Wuhan sealing the city of traffic disruption, it is true that we travel to bring great difficulties.
”刘升说，“现在的勤务和原来完全不一样，24小时不间断岗位。
"Service is now completely different from 24-hour jobs," Liu said.
疫情结束后，我要请中队全员吃烧烤，大家太辛苦了。
After the epidemic, I want to invite the entire squadron to eat barbecue, everyone is too hard.
”融雪工陈建国2月15日，武汉断崖式降温，狂风大雪。
Snow melt worker Chen Jianguo Feb. 15, Wuhan bluff-style cooling, the wind snow.
武昌中南清洁队陈建国负责八一路融雪工作。
Wuchang Zhongnan cleaning team Chen Jianguo in charge of eight road melting snow work.
疫情期间，他每晚8点工作到第二天早上8点，对负责区域进行消杀毒及清扫工作。
During the outbreak, he worked from 8 a.m. to 8 a.m. each night to decontaminate and clean up the area he was responsible for.
“虽然是夜间，平日里武汉车流不息，如今，一个人都见不着。
"Although it is the night, usually Wuhan traffic flow, now, a person can not see.
但每天在负责的洪山体育馆方舱外做消杀毒时，心里倍感骄傲，能为防疫抗疫尽绵薄之力。
But every day in charge of Hongshan stadium outside the cabin to do antivirus, the heart feel proud, can do little to fight against the epidemic.
”滴滴司机胡建斌封城之后，滴滴车队的队长发起招募“医护保障车队”，免费接送武汉医务工作者，胡建斌第一个报名。
After drip-drip driver Hu Jianbin sealed the city, drip team leaders launched a campaign to recruit "medical support convoys," free transport Wuhan medical workers, Hu Jianbin first registration.
“这种时刻，作为武汉人就是本能啊，必须的啊！”胡建斌说，“本来计划和我老婆西藏自驾游的，希望疫情结束后尽早实现。
"This kind of moment, as Wuhan people is instinctive, necessary ah!" Hu Jianbin said, "I had planned to drive in Tibet with my wife, hope to achieve the end of the epidemic as soon as possible.
”小区保安刘勇刘勇家在孝感农村，1月23日封城当天回到武汉值班，已经连续工作20多天，每天执勤站岗12个小时以上。
Xiao Yong Liu Yongjia, a residential security guard, returned to Wuhan on January 23, the day the city was closed, and has been on duty for more than 20 consecutive days, standing sentry duty for more than 12 hours a day.
他很担心家里两个孩子的安全，期待着疫情结束能回家团圆。
He was worried about the safety of his two children and looked forward to the end of the epidemic.
“我们社区的情况控制得还不错，业主也都很理解和支持我们，之前还有业主自发地送给我们三包口罩，真的挺感动。
"The situation in our community is well under control and the owners understand and support us. There were three bags of masks that were given to us by the owners on their own initiative.
